  "prompt": "Can I take modafinil with adderall?",
  "response": "Combining medications like modafinil and Adderall should be done with caution and under the supervision of a healthcare professional. Both medications are stimulants and can increase the risk of side effects such as increased heart rate, increased blood pressure, anxiety, insomnia, and other issues related to overstimulation.\n\nIf you are considering taking both medications, it's essential to discuss this with your doctor. They can evaluate your specific situation, consider potential interactions, and monitor your response to the combination to ensure your safety. Do not self-medicate or make changes to your medication regimen without professional guidance.",
